comment: This has been such a great series - feel so lucky to have stumbled upon these videos and Adriene's channel. I can't stop doing forward folds and downward dogs wherever I am! Big love.

I used to hate yoga, my short upper body, belly fat and huge chest prevented me from breathing when I bent over.  The yoga poses were challenging to breathe and I totally felt discouraged.  My friend challenged me to 90 days of yoga and I took it on! I found Adriene's 30 days of yoga and decided to do each day 3 times before moving on to the next day.  I was so glad I did, it allowed me to go at a slower pace and get better on the moves.  I added diet and exercise along the way and lost some weight!  I still can't breathe when I do child's pose, or forward fold, but I feel so much better.  I have been converted thanks to Adriene's positive energy. I am looking forward to trying her other 30 day videos.
Namaste, Adriene. You're such an amazing person. <3

I started doing this yoga challenge to help decrease my pain, as I have been recently diagnosed with fibromyalgia. By Day 23 I started to realize that I don't really have control over my pain, and that yoga may never make it go away. It was a little discouraging, especially reading all the comments about decreases in pain. But all that meant was that my intention for doing yoga changed. Now it's about strengthening my body and being able to appreciate what it can do regardless of the pain I'm in, and finding peace in that. I'm honoured to be on this journey with all of you.

I used to run competitive long distance before a severe calf injury that I've been trying to recover for 6 years. This challenge and practice has built more strength, flexibility and resilience than years of physio! Why isn't everyone doing this!

Too true Adriene.... the hardest part we've already done and that's starting. Even though I like yoga, it doesn't give me that big dopamine rush that i jump up and wanna do it. I've found very little of what's good for me, gives me those dopamine spikes so then I think, yoga today, or home work out today or I have to catch up on the project today or I have to do maths... and really I often procrastinate pretty bad and will instead waste a lot of my time on social media as my mind believes the dopamine is there through the hope of messages to me or something lol. But really the good stuff for us is often the stuff we don't want to do and we need that will power to lead to consistency which then over time turns into an habit. My mind is still like...why should i do x y z when i don't get excited to do it? But you find when you push through and get on the other side, you are glad you did it and know it's better than just sitting on social media but the same thing plays out again and again.... so keep going guys, keep pushing! Thank you Adriene ;) You'd be like my ideal yoga partner.... I can see us now going out for a organic fruit smoothie and heading back to yours and getting on the mat together :P

Day 25 ‚úîÔ∏è Hello friends! Today's practice reminded me of a saying from Alan Watts: "You're under no obligation to be the same person you were 5 minutes ago."  And here we are 25 days later; many of us are not the same person we were 25 days ago--and even if we''ve been off and on, time still flows and we constantly change--and eventually we get to where we need to be. Life can be a lot of things: a journey, a b*tch, a marathon, etc.; each one of us has a different word for it, but whatever we choose to call it, let's make sure to make it the best version of that.
